{
  "texts": [
    "Extending the access intimacy developed between us, Priscila has had to step into the breach, to support accessibility for Ben both within and externally to the workplace.",
    "What we have offered in this paper is a way of reframing how HEIs orientate to EDI by working with the idea of belonging-a significant cultural development relevant to both staff as much as it is for students.",
    "We have highlighted in particular both the significance of relationality in the workplace and accessibility for those of us who readily do not have it.",
    "We have gone about this by presenting our shared narrative, one that explains how the access intimacy developed between us-a disabled researcher and an accessibility support assistant-enables us to navigate the physical, digital, relational and structural dimensions of an HEI which present ongoing barriers to accessibility in their current configuration.",
    "Not only does Ben benefit from our interactions, but Priscila too has felt empowered, and she has identified skills to create, advocate and negotiate that had not been recognised throughout her time studying at the institution."
  ]
}